  </td>

  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><b><font face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;">OFG
  BANCORP</font></b><font face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;"><br>
  <br>
  &nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>

  <td width=42% style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">

  July 24, 2015</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=top width=5% style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:115%;">By:&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=3 width=53% style="border:none;border-bottom:solid black 1.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">

<body link=blue vlink=purple><a name="page_1"></a><DIV bclPageBorder STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in">

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align=right style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:right;"><b><font face="Times New Roman,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:10.0pt;line-height:150%;">Exhibit 99</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><img height=69 id="Picture 1" src="maindocument001x0x0.jpg" width=319>&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><b><font color=#F5821F face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:18.0pt;line-height:normal;">OFG Bancorp Reports 2Q15 Results</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">SAN JUAN, Puerto
Rico, July 24, 2015 &#8211; OFG Bancorp (NYSE: OFG) today reported results for the
second quarter ended June 30, 2015.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">Jos&#233; Rafael
Fern&#225;ndez, President, Chief Executive Officer, and Vice Chairman of the Board,
commented, &#8220;While a few quarter specific items caused us to post a loss in
2Q15, our core business performed well and capital continues to be strong.&#8221;</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><b><font color=#A7A9AC face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:normal;">2Q15 Highlights</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Loss of
$6.6 million, or ($0.15) per share, compared to a loss of $6.5 million, or
($0.14) per share, in the preceding quarter, and a profit of $17.8 million, or
$0.38 per share diluted, in the year ago quarter.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Compared
to 1Q15, 2Q15 results were adversely impacted by:</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Courier New" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">o</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Absence of $4.2 million in tax
free interest income from loans to the Puerto Rico Electric Power Authority
(PREPA) and the Puerto Rico Aqueduct and Sewer Authority (PRASA).</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.75in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">1.</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">PREPA:
Interest payments on the $200 million loan, which is on non-accrual status, are
being applied to the principal.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.75in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">2.</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">PRASA: The
$75 million remaining balance was paid-off on June 1, 2015.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Courier New" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">o</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">$10.2 million increase in FDIC
commercial loss share amortization (from $13.1 million to $23.2 million)
related to the scheduled expiration of the Eurobank commercial loss sharing
agreement with the FDIC. Going forward, the loss share amortization for
remaining residential mortgages should be significantly lower.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Courier New" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">o</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">$4.5 million of additional
loss in Other Real Estate Owned (OREO) due to revised collateral values as part
of ongoing and proactive de-risking efforts.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Partially
offsetting the above was:</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Courier New" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">o</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">$26.7 million decline in the
total provision for loan and lease losses. This reflects no additional PREPA
provision ($24.0 million in 1Q15) because the government utility and its
creditors are actively working on a repayment agreement. Additionally, no
provision was required on FDIC covered commercial loans ($4.8 million in 1Q15).</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Courier New" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">o</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Continued growth of the
Oriental Bank franchise through the opening of new retail deposit accounts,
reduced cost of total deposits, and strong levels of core non-interest fee
revenues and loan production.</font></p>


<DIV bclFooter>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
</DIV><HR noshade STYLE="page-break-after: always" align="center" width="100%" size=2><a name="page_2"></a><DIV bclPageBorder STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in">

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Courier New" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">o</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Improved credit, with declines
in net charge-offs, total delinquencies and non-performing loans.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Puerto
Rico central government and public corporation balances declined 20.7% to
$301.3 million at June 30, 2015 from $380.1 million at March 31, 2015. This
excludes $214.0 million in term loans to five municipal governments that are
completely separate entities with their own sources of tax revenues.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Tangible
book value and book value per common share declined to $14.67 and $16.81 from
$15.12 and $17.25, respectively, at March 31, 2015. Regulatory capital ratios
continued to be significantly above requirements for a well-capitalized
institution.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><b><font color=#A7A9AC face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:normal;">CEO Comment</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">In commenting on
2Q15 results, Mr. Fern&#225;ndez stated, &#8220;This quarter demonstrates our discipline
in navigating one of the most difficult operating environments in banking
today.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">&#8220;Our core
business performed well as we continued to grow Oriental Bank&#8217;s franchise
serving the commercial and consumer sectors. We experienced strong generation
of quality loans with good pricing discipline, strong fee revenue levels, and
good core expense management. Oriental&#8217;s retail deposit base and mortgage and
consumer loan businesses continued to benefit from successful marketing
attracting new customers. In addition, credit continued to improve as
evidenced, among other things, by lower provisions and net charge-offs while we
maintained provisions at 1.20-1.25% of net charge-offs, increasing the
allowance levels.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">&#8220;However, the
absence of tax-free interest income from the PREPA and PRASA loans was a drag
on NIM and earnings in general. With the scheduled expiration of our commercial
loss share agreement with the FDIC, we incurred a final write down of the
remaining amortization asset for covered commercial loans. In addition, we
de-risked our non-covered portfolio by updating valuations of certain
underlying collaterals and adopted a restitution program in our broker-dealer
subsidiary.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">&#8220;Looking ahead,
prevailing economic conditions in Puerto Rico are challenging and uncertain.
Our strategy is to be vigilant in managing our risk exposure and the factors
under our control. We urge the Central Government to act quickly and in
cooperation with the investment community to restart the Puerto Rico economy,
which has now been stalled for nearly a decade.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">&#8220;Our ultimate
goals remain the same: build the Oriental franchise, further affirming our
reputation as the best bank in Puerto Rico; maximize our profitability and
capital; preserve our flexibility to pursue strategic alternatives; and deploy
our strong capital base to increase shareholder return in a sustainable
manner.&#8221;</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><b><font color=#A7A9AC face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:normal;">2Q15 Income Statement Highlights</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><i><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">The following
compares data for the second quarter 2015 to the first quarter 2015 unless
otherwise noted.</font></i></p>


<DIV bclFooter>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
</DIV><HR noshade STYLE="page-break-after: always" align="center" width="100%" size=2><a name="page_3"></a><DIV bclPageBorder STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in">

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Total
interest income</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
declined $7.6 million to $99.4 million. This reflected:</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Courier New" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">o</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Lower loan income from PREPA
($3.6 million) and PRASA ($0.6 million), as noted above, and from covered loans
($2.8 million) as balances continued to pay down.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Courier New" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">o</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Growth in loan income from all
other originated loans offsetting declines in all other acquired non-covered
loans.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Courier New" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">o</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">$0.6 million in higher premium
amortization on investment securities.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Total
interest expense </font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">fell
slightly to $17.1 million as we continued to improve the deposit funding
profile with decreases in rates.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Net
Interest Margin </font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">declined
to 4.92% from 5.42%, primarily reflecting the loss of income from the PREPA and
PRASA loans.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Provision
for loan and lease losses </font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">fell
$26.7 million to $15.5 million. This reflected no additional PREPA and covered
loan provisioning, as previously mentioned, and $1.3 million decline in
provision on other originated and acquired loans.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Total
core non-interest income</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
increased slightly to $19.4 million. This reflected increased or sustained
levels of revenue across the board in wealth management, banking services and
mortgage banking activity.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">FDIC
indemnification asset amortization</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
increased $10.2 million, as mentioned above, to $23.2 million. The
indemnification asset was $22.7 million at June 30, 2015 versus $75.2 million
at March 31, 2015.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Non-interest
expenses</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
increased $8.1 million, to $64.4 million. This primarily reflected the
following non-recurring expenses:</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">1.</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">The aforementioned $4.5
million increased OREO loss and $1.8 million restitution program by our
broker-dealer subsidiary.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">2.</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </font><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">$1.1 million to close a branch
and other quarter specific expenses.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><b><font color=#A7A9AC face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:normal;">2Q15 Business Activity Highlights</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><i><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">The following
compares data for the second quarter 2015 to the first quarter 2015 unless
otherwise noted.</font></i></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Total
new loan production (excluding renewals) </font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">increased 19.7% to $286.7 million.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Commercial
loan production</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
increased 40.7% to $120.5 million, reflecting the pipeline that was starting to
build in 1Q15.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Residential
mortgage loan production</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">,
most of which is sold into the secondary market, increased 5.0% to $64.8
million as Oriental continued to expand its market share.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Consumer
loan production</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
increased 52.3% to $39.8 million due to improved marketing and a larger client
base.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Auto
loan production</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
declined 6.6% to $61.5 million. This reflects increased competition from the
captive finance arms of manufacturers, and our own initiative to increase FICO
score requirements to improve credit. </font></p>


<DIV bclFooter>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
</DIV><HR noshade STYLE="page-break-after: always" align="center" width="100%" size=2><a name="page_4"></a><DIV bclPageBorder STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in">

<DIV bclHeader>


<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:center 3.25in right 6.5in;"><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>


</DIV>
<p style="margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Cost of
deposits </font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">declined
5 basis points to 0.65% from 1Q15 and 22 basis points from 0.87% in 2Q14, as a
result of reductions in demand, savings, time and brokered deposit rates.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><b><font color=#A7A9AC face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;">June
30, 2015 Balance Sheet Highlights</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><i><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">The following
compares data as of June 30, 2015 to March 31, 2015 or for the second quarter
2015 to the first quarter 2015 unless otherwise noted.</font></i></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Average
interest earning assets</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
increased slightly to $6.71 billion. This reflected an increase in total
investments as OFG reinvested excess cash from repayments of loans and
investment securities, and increased originated loans, all of which more than
offset declines in acquired and covered loans due to normal pay downs.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Total
stockholders&#8217; equity</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
declined $24.8 million to $911.6 million. This primarily reflected a $10.9
million decrease in retained earnings and a $10.0 million decrease in other
comprehensive income.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><b><font color=#A7A9AC face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:normal;">Credit Quality Highlights</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><i><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">The following
compares data for the second quarter 2015 to the first quarter 2015 unless
otherwise noted.</font></i></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Net
charge-offs </font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">declined
10.1% to $7.7 million as we continued to fine tune our collection efforts to
evolving credit trends. Net charge-offs have declined three quarters in a row.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Total
delinquency</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;"> </font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">rate&nbsp;</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
declined 88 basis points to 7.72% primarily due to improvements in the
mortgage, consumer and auto loan portfolios. The total delinquency rate has
declined three quarters in a row.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Non-performing
loan rate </font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">declined
20 basis points to 10.44%.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Allowance
for loan and lease losses</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
increased $2.2 million to $79.0 million. This resulted in coverage of 2.67% of
loans held for investment compared to 2.64%.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><b><font color=#A7A9AC face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:normal;">Capital Position</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><i><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">The following
compares data for the second quarter 2015 to the first quarter 2015.</font></i></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Tangible
common equity to total tangible assets</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">
declined to 8.91% from 9.29% based on a 3.6% decrease in tangible common equity
to $650.9 million and a 0.5% increase in tangible assets to $7.3 billion.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Common
Equity Tier 1 Capital Ratio (using Basel III methodology)</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;"> was 12.25% compared to
12.63%.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.25in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:-.25in;"><font face=Symbol lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">&#183;</font><font face="Times New Roman" lang=EN-US style="font-size:7.0pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</font><b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">Total
risk-based capital ratio </font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:12.0pt;">declined
to 17.40% from 17.69% based on a 2.1% decline in total risk-based capital to
$868.6 million and a 0.4% decline in total risk weighted assets to $5.0
billion.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><b><font color=#A7A9AC face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;">Forward
Looking Statements</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">The information
included in this document contains certain forward-looking statements within
the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. These
statements are based on management&#8217;s current expectations and involve certain
risks and uncertainties that may cause actual results to differ materially from
those expressed in the forward-looking statements.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">Factors that
might cause such a difference include, but are not limited to (i) the rate of
growth in the economy and employment levels, as well as general business and
economic conditions; (ii) changes in interest rates, as well as the magnitude
of such changes; (iii) a credit default by the government of Puerto Rico; (iv)
the fiscal and monetary policies of the federal government and its agencies;
(v) changes in federal bank regulatory and supervisory policies, including
required levels of capital; (vi) the relative strength or weakness of the
consumer and commercial credit sectors and of the real estate market in Puerto
Rico; (vii) the performance of the stock and bond markets; (viii) competition
in the financial services industry; and (ix) possible legislative, tax or
regulatory changes.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">For a discussion
of such factors and certain risks and uncertainties to which OFG is subject,
see OFG&#8217;s annual report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31, 2014, as
well as its other filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.
Other than to the extent required by applicable law, including the requirements
of applicable securities laws, OFG assumes no obligation to update any
forward-looking statements to reflect occurrences or unanticipated events or
circumstances after the date of such statements.</font></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><b><font color=#A7A9AC face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;">About
OFG Bancorp</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:justify;"><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">Now in its 51<sup>st</sup>
year in business, OFG Bancorp is a diversified financial holding company that
operates under U.S. and Puerto Rico banking laws and regulations.&#160; Its three
principal subsidiaries, Oriental Bank, Oriental Financial Services and Oriental
Insurance, provide a full range of commercial, consumer and mortgage banking
services, as well as financial planning, trust, insurance, investment brokerage
and investment banking services, primarily in Puerto Rico, through 52 financial
centers and 332 ATMs. Investor information can be found at www.ofgbancorp.com.</font><font face=Calibri,sans-serif lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">

&nbsp;</font><p align=center style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=#F5821F face="Futura Bk BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;"># # #</font></p>

</p><p style="margin-bottom:10.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><b><font color=#A7A9AC face="Futura Md BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%;">Contacts</font></b></p>

<p style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><b><font color=#F5821F face="Futura Bk BT,sans-serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">Puerto Rico:</font></b><font face="Century Schoolbook,serif" lang=EN-US style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;"> Alexandra L&#243;pez (allopez@orientalbank.com), OFG Bancorp, (787) 522-6970</font></p>

  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;page-break-after:avoid;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>

  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;page-break-after:avoid;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  </td>

  </td>

  ratio. The table below provides the details of the calculation of our

  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=11% style="height:15.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:119.25pt;">
  <td nowrap width=6% style="background:#DBEEF4;height:119.25pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(1)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 nowrap width=94% style="background:#DBEEF4;border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:119.25pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">We use the term &quot;acquired loans&quot; to refer to loans
  acquired from the BBVAPR acquisition (December 18, 2012) and covered loans
  acquired in the Eurobank FDIC-Assisted acquisition (April 30, 2010), recorded
  at fair value at acquisition. The majority of these loans acquired are
  subsequently accounted for based on estimated cash flows expected to be
  collected over the life of the loans (under the accounting standard known as
  ASC 310-30). Because the guidance takes into consideration future credit
  losses expected to be incurred over the life of the loans, there are no
  charge-offs or an allowance associated with this loans unless the estimated
  cash flows expected to be collected decrease subsequent to acquisition. In
  addition, these loans are not classified as delinquent or nonperforming even
  though the customer may be contractually past due because we expect that we
  will fully collect the carrying value of these loans. Acquired loans also
  include loans acquired in the BBVAPR acquisition that were accounted for
  under the provisions of ASC 310-20, which at the end of the reporting period
  still have unamortized premium or discount. The fair value of these loans
  already include a credit mark for losses estimated on these loans.&#160; The
  allowance for loan and lease losses for these loans consider such marks
  applied. The accounting and classification of these loans may significantly
  alter some of our reported credit quality metrics. We therefore supplement
  certain reported credit quality metrics with metrics adjusted to exclude the
  impact of these acquired loans. Loans acquired in the BBVAPR acquisition that
  were accounted for under the provisions of ASC 310-20, which had fully
  amortized their premium or discount recorded at the date of acquisition at the
  end of the reporting period, are removed from the acquired loans category.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:9.0pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(2)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 valign=bottom width=94% style="border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Total banking and wealth management revenues.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:28.5pt;">
  <td nowrap width=6% style="background:#DBEEF4;height:28.5pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(3)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 nowrap width=94% style="background:#DBEEF4;border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:28.5pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">During Q1 2015, the Company placed its $200 million
  participation in a fuel purchase line of credit with the Puerto Rico Electric
  Power Authority (PREPA) on non-accrual status and recorded a $24.0 million
  provision for loan and lease losses, which is part of the overall quarterly
  provision for loan and lease losses.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:11.25pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:11.25pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(4)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 valign=bottom width=94% style="border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:11.25pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Calculated based on net (loss) income available to common
  shareholders divided by average common shares outstanding for the period.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:18.75pt;">
  <td nowrap width=6% style="background:#DBEEF4;height:18.75pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(5)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 nowrap width=94% style="background:#DBEEF4;border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:18.75pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Calculated based on net (loss) income available to common
  shareholders plus the preferred dividends on the convertible preferred stock,
  divided by total average common shares outstanding and equivalents for the
  period as if converted.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:9.0pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">

  dividend per common share to $0.10 per share during Q4 2014.</font></p>
  </td>

<tr style="height:19.5pt;">

  </td>
 <td colspan=12 nowrap width=94% style="background:#DBEEF4;border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:19.5pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Tangible book value per common share is a non-GAAP measure calculated
  based on tangible common equity divided by common shares outstanding. See
  &quot;Table 9: Reconciliation of Non-GAAP Measures and Calculation of
  Regulatory Capital Measures&quot; for additional information.</font></p>
  </td>

<tr style="height:20.25pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:20.25pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">

  all acquired loans. Acquired loans, including those accounted for under ASC

<tr style="height:10.5pt;">

<tr style="height:28.5pt;">
  <td nowrap width=6% style="background:#DBEEF4;height:28.5pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(23)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 nowrap width=94% style="background:#DBEEF4;border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:28.5pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Loans accounted for under ASC 310-30 (Loans acquired with
  deteriorated credit quality, including those by analogy), including covered
  loans, are considered to be performing due to the application of the
  accretion method, in which these loans will accrete interest income over the
  remaining life of the loans using estimated cash flow analyses. Therefore,
  they are not included as non-performing loans.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:83.25pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:83.25pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(24)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 valign=bottom width=94% style="border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:83.25pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">During Q1 2015, the Company implemented the New Capital Rules,
  which incorporates Basel III Capital Requirements. The New Capital Rules
  revise the definitions and the components of regulatory capital, as well as
  address other issues affecting the numerator in banking institutions&#8217;
  regulatory capital ratios. The New Capital Rules also address asset risk
  weights and other matters affecting the denominator in banking institutions&#8217;
  regulatory capital ratios and replace the existing general risk-weighting
  approach with a more risk-sensitive approach. The New Capital Rules are
  effective for OFG Bancorp and Oriental Bank on January 1, 2015, subject to
  phase-in periods for certain of their components and other provisions. Among
  other matters, the New Capital Rules: (i) introduce a new capital measure
  called &#8220;Common Equity Tier 1&#8221; (&#8220;CET1&#8221;) and related regulatory capital ratio
  of CET1 to risk-weighted assets; (ii) specify that Tier 1 capital consists of
  CET1 and &#8220;Additional Tier 1 capital&#8221; instruments meeting certain revised
  requirements; (iii) mandate that most deductions/adjustments to regulatory
  capital measures be made to CET1 and not to the other components of capital;
  and (iv) expand the scope of the deductions from and adjustments to capital
  as compared to existing regulations. </font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:9.0pt;">
  <td nowrap width=6% style="background:#DBEEF4;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(25)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 nowrap width=94% style="background:#DBEEF4;border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Total risk-based capital equals the sum of Tier 1 capital and
  Tier 2 capital.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:18.75pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:18.75pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(26)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 valign=bottom width=94% style="border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:18.75pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Common equity Tier 1 capital ratio is a regulatory capital
  measure calculated based on Common equity Tier 1 capital divided by
  risk-weighted assets.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:9.0pt;">
  <td nowrap width=6% style="background:#DBEEF4;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(27)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 nowrap width=94% style="background:#DBEEF4;border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Tier 1 risk-based capital ratio is a regulatory capital measure
  calculated based on Tier 1 capital divided by risk-weighted assets.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:9.0pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(28)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 valign=bottom width=94% style="border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Total risk-based capital ratio is a regulatory capital measure
  calculated based on Total risk-based capital divided by risk-weighted assets.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:9.0pt;">
  <td nowrap width=6% style="background:#DBEEF4;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(29)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 nowrap width=94% style="background:#DBEEF4;border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Leverage capital ratio is a regulatory capital measure
  calculated based on Tier 1 capital divided by average assets, after certain
  adjustments.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:9.0pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(30)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 valign=bottom width=94% style="border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">The Company decided to elect the opt-out option to continue to exclude
  AOCI items from regulatory capital calculation.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:9.0pt;">
  <td nowrap width=6% style="background:#DBEEF4;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(31)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 nowrap width=94% style="background:#DBEEF4;border:none;border-bottom:none black 1.0pt;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">Amounts based on transition provisions for regulatory capital
  deductions and adjustments of 40% for 2015.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:19.5pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:19.5pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(32)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 valign=bottom width=94% style="height:19.5pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">During Q2 2015, the Company sold mortgage servicing rights on
  $653.5 million mortgage loans to Scotiabank PR. As a result, the delinquent
  GNMA's buy-back option program loans and corresponding liability decreased
  $30.5 million from Q1 2015.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:9.0pt;">
  <td nowrap width=6% style="background:#DBEEF4;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(33)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 nowrap width=94% style="background:#DBEEF4;height:9.0pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">The FDIC Indemnification Asset for projected claimable losses on
  non-single family residential loans loss-share period ended in June 30, 2015.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:29.25pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:29.25pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">(34)</font></p>
  </td>
 <td colspan=12 valign=bottom width=94% style="height:29.25pt;padding:0in 2.0pt 0in 2.0pt;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">During Q2 2015, the Company had 54 more net exits from
  foreclosed real estate amounting to approximately $10 million than in Q1
  2015. In addition, the Company had 174 less net entries in repossessed auto
  amounting to approximately $1.3 million compared to Q1 2015. The remaining
  decrease is due to a decline in value of foreclosed real estate and other
  repossessed properties.</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
<tr style="height:9.0pt;">
  <td valign=top width=6% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p align=center style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;text-align:center;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:6.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=40% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=3% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=6% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=1% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=3% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=10% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=2% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=3% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=10% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=2% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>

 <td valign=bottom width=3% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 <td valign=bottom width=11% style="height:9.0pt;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;">
  <p style="margin-bottom:.0001pt;margin-left:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-top:0in;"><font color=black face="Times New Roman,serif" style="font-size:7.0pt;line-height:normal;">&nbsp;</font></p>
